President Obama has issued a proclamation recognizing Earth Day, which is celebrated on April 22nd each year. He highlights the importance of this day and the need to address climate change, which he believes is the biggest threat to future generations. The President emphasizes that human activity is the primary driver of climate change and that it will have profound impacts on all of humanity. He mentions the steps his administration has taken to combat climate change, such as proposing carbon pollution limits for power plants and partnering with communities to prepare for its impacts. The President also mentions the United States' commitment to reducing greenhouse gas emissions and investing in clean energy. He calls on all Americans to participate in programs and activities that protect the environment and contribute to a healthy, sustainable future.